members="%5B%7B%22image%22%3A%225293%22%2C%22name%22%3A%22Jose%20Aldo%22%2C%22position%22%3A%22Car%20Parts%20Manager%22%2C%22desc%22%3A%22I%20regularly%20order%20spare%20parts%20for%20my%20clients%20and%20for%20my%20auto%20parts%20in%20Pitstop%2C%20I%20am%20satisfied%20with%20the%20attitude%20of%20specialist%20to%20my%20work.%20Thank%20you%20for%20your%20attention%20and%20not%20a%20little%20importantly%20low%20prices.%20I%20advise%20everyone%20and%20even%20in%20another%20country.%22%2C%22phone%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22email%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22skype%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22facebook%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22twitter%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22link%22%3A%22url%3Ahttps%253A%252F%252Fpitstop.true-emotions.studio%252Fabout-us%252F%7C%7C%7C%22%7D%2C%7B%22image%22%3A%225292%22%2C%22name%22%3A%22Kate%20Smith%22%2C%22position%22%3A%22Car%20Parts%20Manager%22%2C%22desc%22%3A%22Yes%2C%20by%20the%20way%2C%20friends!%20I%20forgot%20to%20mention%20the%20prices!%20Prices!%20Friends!%20Prices%20are%20Really%20low%20and%20adequate!%20It%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20much%20cheaper%20for%20me%20with%20delivery%20and%20other%20expenses%20than%20I%20would%20take%20in%20the%20local%20market!%20Here%2C%20now%20everything%20seems%20to%20be%20done!%22%2C%22phone%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22email%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22skype%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22facebook%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22instagram%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22link%22%3A%22url%3Ahttps%253A%252F%252Fpitstop.true-emotions.studio%252Fabout-us%252F%7Ctitle%3AAbout%2520Us%7C%7C%22%7D%2C%7B%22image%22%3A%225294%22%2C%22name%22%3A%22Jared%20Snow%22%2C%22position%22%3A%22Car%20Parts%20Manager%22%2C%22desc%22%3A%22Dear%20friends%2C%20hello%20everyone!%20I%20would%20like%20to%20share%20my%20opinion%20about%20this%20company%2C%20namely%20about%20the%20Pitstop%20company%20in%20New%20York.%20I%20ordered%20a%20spare%20part%20for%20my%20car%20from%20this%20company.%20There%20were%20some%20doubts%2C%20not%20every%20time%20you%20buy%20it%20over%20the%20Internet.%22%2C%22phone%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22skype%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22facebook%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22instagram%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22link%22%3A%22url%3Ahttps%253A%252F%252Fpitstop.true-emotions.studio%252Fabout-us%252F%7Ctitle%3ALED%2520headlights%2520for%2520a%2520sports%2520car%7C%7C%22%7D%2C%7B%22image%22%3A%225293%22%2C%22name%22%3A%22Eliza%20Snow%22%2C%22position%22%3A%22Car%20Parts%20Manager%22%2C%22desc%22%3A%22I%20did%20not%20find%20a%20Geely%20Atlas%20car%20in%20the%20catalog%2C%20although%20it%20is%20very%20common%20in%20USA.%20In%20addition%2C%20when%20selecting%20a%20wiper%20blade%2C%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20sort%20by%20mounting%20method%20and%20size.%20Otherwise%2C%20the%20service%20is%20not%20bad%20and%20the%20prices%20are%20pleasant.%22%2C%22phone%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22email%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22facebook%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22twitter%22%3A%22%2F%22%2C%22link%22%3A%22url%3Ahttps%253A%252F%252Fpitstop.true-emotions.studio%252Fabout-us%252F%7C%7C%7C%22%7D%5D"][/vc_column][/vc_row]

And manufacturers of car care products keep pace with the times. To date, a full range of products for caring for your car is on sale. All such funds can be conditionally divided into categories and each of them can be considered. These shampoos are designed specifically to remove a variety of impurities. Special shampoos easily remove even oil residues and at the same time reliably protect the body paintwork. Perfectly wash a car, prevent corrosion of the body and polish the shampoos, which contain wax in their composition. These shampoos are completely safe for your hands.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1589015217520{background-color: #ffffff !important;}"][vc_column gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1611410109785{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column_text]
In order to add shine to your car, you can use polishes and pastes with abrasive particles. They are able to remove many stains, including rust, and naturally polish the surface. With these tools, it is even possible to smooth out minor scratches on the paint. After processing with polishes or paste, the surface acquires water and dirt repellency.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding M" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Grinding pastes have a more serious effect. With their help, you can effectively get rid of weathered and dull surfaces. Pastes are used to combat scratches and paint defects. The body can be painted without additional treatment if it has been thoroughly treated with grinding paste beforehand.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding S" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1561394194196{border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_single_image image="7505" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616770681668{padding-right: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="7504" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616770690648{padding-left: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="Products intended for the car interior and glass" size="pix-s" position="text-left" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]A wider range is provided by products intended for the car interior and glass. In the cabin there are many elements made of plastic, which eventually loses its attractive appearance. By using plastic products in the salon, you can give a new and bright life to matt surfaces and surfaces that have been discolored in the sun. Plastic products clean not only plastic, but also rubber interior parts. When using them, the plastic elements take on their previous appearance, and at the same time a greasy film does not form on them. Interior elements stop creaking.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="You can buy a complex remedy" size="pix-s" position="text-left" show_decor="off" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]They are designed to clean immediately panels and upholstery. They are able to get rid of dust and unpleasant odors in the car interior. But to care for a leather salon, you need special care products that will preserve the skin and make it soft and supple.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" item.title: How to find out the part number for your car?
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column_text]If you have been using the car for a long time, replacement parts cannot be avoided. And so that it is not too frequent, it is better to buy original parts. All parts are linked to the VIN-code of a particular car, and each has an article - a unique alphanumeric number. Usually it is embossed directly on the parts, but after some time it may change due to modernization.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="Who should you contact first?" size="pix-s" position="text-left" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding M" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]To find out if the part number that interests you has changed, you need to contact either a service center or a company that specializes in the delivery of customized auto parts. You can find the required part: by the VIN-code of the car, on the electronic base, by catalog number.If your machine is not new, the corresponding parts must be ordered online. [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%22gradient_color%22%3A%22%23ffffff%22%7D%5D"][vc_column gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1611409759417{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column_text]
Using the electronic base of articles, you can find out the number of a certain part by entering the VIN code of the car into the search engine. You can buy a disc with this database, but the information it contains will become outdated over time. Any auto part can be identified by VIN-code.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding M" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]On the websites of online stores, using the search service, you can find parts by make and year of manufacture of the car. But do not forget to clarify the relevance of such information. Non-original spare parts also have numbers and markings. Therefore, one must be able to distinguish analogs from fakes: the latter can be significantly inferior to duplicates in quality.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding S" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1561394194196{border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_single_image image="7505" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616769778072{padding-right: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="7504" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616769789089{padding-left: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="Why is the part number from the catalog useful?" size="pix-s" position="text-left" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]There are situations when you need a catalog number for a particular part. Indeed, there are many brands and models of cars in the world, therefore, even experienced car owners do not always manage to find the necessary spare part, focusing only on the brand. A catalog number is a unique article assigned to a part by the development company of a particular model. If you know him, it will be easy to find the right parts.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="What other search options are there?" size="pix-s" position="text-left" show_decor="off" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Among its many methods, the most popular is Internet search: it does not require either financial costs or special skills. You just browse the catalogs and look for the parts you want. By shopping this way, you avoid tedious trips to car markets and specialty stores. Yes, delivery is usually paid, but what a time saving! You can also find the necessary spare part by VIN-code.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_tab_acc toggle_type="accordion" collapse="on" rnization.%22%2C%22tab_id_a%22%3A%22491228797%22%7D%2C%7B%22label_a%22%3A%22How%20to%20use%20the%20VIN%20car%20driver%20correctly%3F%22%2C%22content_a%22%3A%22If%20you%20have%20been%20using%20the%20car%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20replacement%20parts%20cannot%20be%20avoided.%20And%20so%20that%20it%20is%20not%20too%20frequent%2C%20it%20is%20better%20to%20buy%20original%20parts.%20All%20parts%20are%20linked%20to%20the%20VIN-code%20of%20a%20particular%20car%2C%20and%20each%20has%20an%20article%20%E2%80%93%20a%20unique%20alphanumeric%20number.%20Usually%20it%20is%20embossed%20directly%20on%20the%20parts%2C%20but%20after%20some%20time%20it%20may%20change%20due%20to%20modernization.%22%2C%22tab_id_a%22%3A%22183026561%22%7D%5D"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding M" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]As you read the VIN, pay attention to the first three characters. The very first of them denotes the country of manufacture, the second denotes the enterprise where the car was manufactured, and the third denotes its type (passenger or truck). Having chosen a specific online store, be sure to check if its catalog contains a complete description of the parts you need. If it is, then feel free to order them. You can return the product to the store until the final order.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: How to choose the right car seat for your child?
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]If you drive a car and have a child, then a child car seat is an essential part of all trips. This is not just a comfortable seat, but reliable protection for your baby in an accident, during sudden maneuvers and braking. A quality car seat protects your child and allows him to develop properly.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="What do parents face when choosing?" size="pix-s" position="text-left" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding M" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]The first thing parents face when they decide to buy a child car seat is which one to choose among such a wide variety. After all, the chair must first of all be safe and reliable. Today, many manufacturers present child car seats on the market. And among such a variegated variety, it is not surprising to get confused in the choice. When buying a car seat for a child, you must adhere to several important rules.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1589015195821{background-color: #ffffff !important;}"][vc_column gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1611409999542{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column_text]
First of all, when choosing a car seat for a child, it is necessary to take into account his age. According to age categories, car seats are divided into classes: Group "0" - armchairs that are similar in design to a cradle. They have a convenient carrying handle and are designed for babies up to one year old; Group "1" and "2" - are classic car seats for children.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding M" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Group "1" and "2" - are classic car seats for children. They have a durable shock-resistant body, a higher headrest and comfortable side parts. Such chairs have been developed for children from 9 months to 4 years old, respectively, and children 3 - 9 years old;  Group "3" - car seats designed for children 6 - 12 years old. They can be represented as a regular car seat or a seat without a backrest.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding S" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1561394194196{border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_single_image image="7505" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616770650351{padding-right: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="7503" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616770661630{padding-left: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="Consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt" size="pix-s" position="text-left" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]But when choosing a car seat, you can come across completely different models designed for the same age. Therefore, when buying a chair, it is important to take into account, in addition to age, the height and weight of the child.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="Design and comfort seat comfort" size="pix-s" position="text-left" show_decor="off" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]It is very important that the child feels comfortable in the car seat. Your trip will be safer if your child feels good and does not distract you from the road. Now you can easily purchase a chair with an anatomical seat, comfortable armrests and an orthopedic insert. There are also models with a table that serves as a belt and with a device for legs. [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_tab_acc toggle_type="accordion" collapse="on" For example, if a baby is a newborn, it is necessary to start unambiguously with a bassinet chair, and only then purchase another chair. If you bought a car when the child is already rather big, you can consider purchasing a universal car seat. For a car seat, safety and reliability should come first. Therefore, all models have the necessary certificates and meet the highest international standards. All car seats have passed independent crash tests.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: How to prepare your car for spring after winter use?
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]What a great time spring. Bright gentle sun, joyful trills of birds and of course down with winter clothes and hello a short skirt. But the guys should take care of their iron horse. Drive after a long winter the car must be prepared for the spring. It is necessary to bring all components and assemblies into conformity after work in severe winter conditions. What should you pay attention to?[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="What should you pay attention to first of all?" size="pix-s" position="text-left" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding M" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]There is a misconception among motorists that if the battery has worked for you with truth and faith all winter, then there will definitely not be any troubles in the warm season. But it is important to take into account that in winter the battery worked at its limit. Therefore, first of all, it is necessary to inspect the terminals for the presence of an oxidation reaction.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1589015207211{background-color: #ffffff !important;}"][vc_column gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1611410070265{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column_text]
Every experienced driver knows that a detailed inspection of the engine is included in the preparations for the spring. After all, it lends itself to regular temperature changes throughout the entire cold period. Parts made of plastic and rubber are subject to the greatest destruction. Such malfunctions provoke oil or antifreeze leakage.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding M" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Another of the most important systems is braking. It also needs to be examined first. It is necessary to change the hoses that are cracked and add brake fluid. Don't miss the need to wash your fuel tank. Many people make a mistake and forget about such a necessity. This can lead to a malfunction of the entire system, which in turn negatively affects the safety of a person in a car.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding S" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1561394194196{border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_single_image image="7503" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616770102562{padding-right: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="7505" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616770112478{padding-left: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="And of course one of the most important is the braking system" size="pix-s" position="text-left" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]It also needs to be examined first. It is necessary to change the hoses that are cracked and add brake fluid. Don't miss the need to wash your fuel tank. Many people make a mistake and forget about such a necessity. This can lead to a malfunction of the entire system, which in turn negatively affects the safety of a person in a car. In winter, municipal services use chemical reagents on the roads to ensure traffic. In this regard, with the arrival of heat, it is necessary to thoroughly wash the car in order to get rid of all kinds of dust and dirt, even in small cracks. Places with damaged paint should be treated with a special agent to prevent corrosion. It is better to paint the chips. Otherwise, the metal will collapse and more serious repairs will be required.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="Be very careful on the very first trips as the roads are still slippery" size="pix-s" position="text-left" show_decor="off" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Pay attention to how the car behaves on the road. Spring can bring many surprises on the tracks. If you feel that the car "leads" to the side at speed, this is most likely a sign that it is necessary to adjust the wheel alignment. This procedure is necessary if you observe significant steering play. All these are signs of the effects of winter.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" item.title: What is the best parking sensor for your car?
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Parktronic allows you to quickly and easily park your car in tight spaces. Sensors built into the bumper send a signal that reflects off objects. Based on the speed at which the signal returns, the system calculates the distance to obstacles and informs the driver.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="How is parking sensors installed?" size="pix-s" position="text-left" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding M" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]On average, the installation of parking sensors takes 2-3 hours (depending on the number of installed sensors, video cameras). Markings are made on the bumper where the sensors will stand (the distance between the sensors should be 35 - 40 cm, height 50 cm from the surface of the asphalt). Holes are made in the bumper according to the markings. [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1589015187538{background-color: #ffffff !important;}"][vc_column gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1611409821665{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column_text]
The sensors are inserted, the edges are treated with a sealant (if desired, the sensors are painted in the color of the bumper The sensors are connected to the electrical control unit and to the reverse gear system. The display is installed in the interior. The electrical control unit is fixed in the luggage compartment. All the wiring is hidden under the finishing material.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding M" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]The electrical control unit is fixed in the luggage compartment. All the wiring is hidden under the finishing material. The masters of our auto shop have extensive experience in installing parking radars on different cars. They will accurately and quickly put parking sensors on your car. [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding S" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D" css=".vc_custom_1561394194196{border-radius: 5px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_single_image image="7512" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616770611777{padding-right: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="7510" img_size="full" style="vc_box_rounded" css=".vc_custom_1616770371890{padding-left: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="Which parking sensor is better to choose?" size="pix-s" position="text-left" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]First of all, the choice of parking sensors depends on the car model. On a small car, it is enough to install 2 sensors on the rear bumper and, if desired, on the front one. For a crossover, it is necessary to install at least 4 sensors on the rear bumper and supplement with a video camera - then the viewing angle will be maximum.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding S" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_title title="The more sensors are installed on the bumper" size="pix-s" position="text-left" show_decor="off" padding="off"][/common_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][vc_column_text]The more they block the viewing angle. The result is no blind spots. There are also parking sensors in the form of an electromagnetic tape, which is glued to the inner surface of the bumper and guarantees you a complete absence of blind spots.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row pix_padding_top="padding No" pix_padding_bottom="padding No" gradient_colors="%5B%7B%7D%5D"][vc_column][common_tab_acc toggle_type="accordion"
